		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2009"></a><br><code>sle2009/paper12</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>Ontological Metamodeling with Explicit Instantiation</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AlfonsLaarman.html">Alfons Laarman</a>, <a href="../profile/IvanKurtev.html">Ivan Kurtev</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_14">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_14</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3e.html"><span class="tagM">T3E: Ontologies</span></a><ul><li> It derives a metalanguage from formal ontology and uses ontological notions (instantiation/generalization) as first-class concepts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> The work proposes a new metalanguage (OGML) for metamodeling beyond abstract syntax.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It argues for more precise conceptual/formal foundations in metamodeling, grounded in ontology theory.
</li></ul></li></ul>
